<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 02 at 4:44PM MDT  by NWS Billings</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Carter
County through 530 PM MDT...
At 443 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking two strong thunderstorms
17 miles southwest of Ridgeway, or 30 miles east of Broadus, moving
northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Ridgeway and Hammond.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
